Version 2 "Certification Trainer"
    rename project "goethe-zertifikat-trainer" > "certification-trainer" (when goethe data are outside project)
    goal of version 2:
        - no "goethe", "Deutsch" specific data, feature
        - reduce dependency with angular if possible
        - i18n added (stored in localstorage, default text is english but can be overriden)
        - certification (goethe) specific data are uploaded in dedicated screen (subset of data can be uploaded, e.g. vocabulary of a1, a2, ...)
        - localstorage could be exported (as today with copy/paste, the tree in the localstorage must be logical, e.g. frontend i18n, certif data, result data)
        - printfriendly available in some screen
        - screens
            - main screen: selection of certifications, footer: language ui selection, license, credits
            - certification main screen: selection of available certif. specific screens, footer: same as main screen
                - link to external site: e.g. alphabet is a dedicated angular js apps
            - localstorage screen as today is hidden
            - basic groups/entries screen (e.g. mathematics, presentations, punctuations, salutations-closings)
            - advanced groups/entries screen (e.g. speech-helpers)
                - config: level field
                - tbd: actual solution with btn or normal index tree (expandable tree)
            - in basic/advanced groups/entries screen, entry can be url
                - anchor second level to jump to jump to actual screen & bookmarkable
            - searched "table" screen: fulltext criteria + level field
                => maybe display entry with several sub list attribute
                => typical uses: vocabulary, grammar (summary of grammar punct + external link to dedicated site)
            - detail screen of entry (if necessary)
            - flashcard screen (one for a flashcard type)
            - flashcard configuration screen (level selection) if needed
    how to save: json data? > export git project as zip to gmail? create unix script to automize this action

